<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFSchauffler1911" class="citation book cs1">Schauffler, Robert Haven (1911). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=HbiFcgAACAAJ"><i>Memorial Day: Its Celebration, Spirit, and Significance as Related in Prose and Verse, with a Non-sectional Anthology of the Civil War</i></a>. BiblioBazaar reprint 2010. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9781176839045" title="Special:BookSources/9781176839045"><bdi>9781176839045</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Memorial+Day%3A+Its+Celebration%2C+Spirit%2C+and+Significance+as+Related+in+Prose+and+Verse%2C+with+a+Non-sectional+Anthology+of+the+Civil+War&amp;rft.pub=BiblioBazaar+reprint+2010&amp;rft.date=1911&amp;rft.isbn=9781176839045&amp;rft.aulast=Schauffler&amp;rft.aufirst=Robert+Haven&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DHbiFcgAACAAJ&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMemorial+Day" class="Z3988"></span></li></ul>
